,{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Native Image Tests**\\n\\nI’m considering that tests should execute under Native Image by default. A no-op fallback might be acceptable. I could set a custom SecurityManager for JVM only, but if setSecurityManager is unsupported in native, I shouldn’t skip the entire test; instead, I could assert the normal public method path. However, this won’t cover all lines. The coverage report likely comes from the JVM run with the SecurityManager. I also need to restore it to avoid global effects. \\n\\nLooks like I should implement a method to handle this, saving the previous manager.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZXFIkoacSFcU8fLWn3cIxKQe|fc_070796f0ad0fea2a0169f521b2915081a2aa398d1a9eb4521e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap java.lang.SecurityManager | rg \"checkMemberAccess|checkPackageAccess|checkPermission\"", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 919, "output": 460, "cacheRead": 61440, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 62819, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777672617169, "responseId": "resp_070796f0ad0fea2a0169f521a9d1c881a29364f4d3fde9e98b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_ZXFIkoacSFcU8fLWn3cIxKQe|fc_070796f0ad0fea2a0169f521b2915081a2aa398d1a9eb4521e", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  public void checkPermission(java.security.Permission);\n  public void checkPermission(java.security.Permission, java.lang.Object);\n  public void checkPackageAccess(java.lang.String);\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777672627025}]}
